sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth2
    participant NotebookCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Workbench<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth Proxy
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS IAM
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Storage as Storage Initializer<br/>HTTPS
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.3
    participant Predictor as Model Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant Client as External Client<br/>HTTPS
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 1: Model Training to Deployment (End-to-End)

    User->>Dashboard: 1. Launch notebook workspace<br/>HTTPS (OAuth Bearer)
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: 2. Create Notebook CR<br/>Kubernetes API
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: 3. Deploy pod with OAuth proxy<br/>Kubernetes API
    NotebookCtrl-->>User: Workbench URL

    User->>Notebook: 4. Access JupyterLab<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Note over Notebook: Develop and train model<br/>(PyTorch/TensorFlow)

    Notebook->>S3: 5. Save trained model<br/>HTTPS (AWS SDK)
    S3-->>Notebook: Model stored

    User->>Dashboard: 6. Create InferenceService<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Dashboard->>KServe: 7. Create InferenceService CR<br/>Kubernetes API

    KServe->>Storage: 8. Trigger storage init<br/>Kubernetes API
    Storage->>S3: 9. Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS (AWS IAM)
    S3-->>Storage: Model files
    Storage-->>Predictor: 10. Copy to shared volume

    KServe->>Predictor: 11. Create predictor deployment<br/>Kubernetes API
    KServe->>Gateway: 12. Configure Istio routing<br/>VirtualService CR

    Client->>Gateway: 13. POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS (Bearer Token)
    Gateway->>Predictor: 14. Forward request<br/>mTLS (service mesh)
    Predictor->>Predictor: 15. Run inference
    Predictor-->>Gateway: 16. Prediction result
    Gateway-->>Client: 17. JSON response<br/>HTTPS

    Predictor->>Prometheus: 18. Export metrics (/metrics)<br/>HTTP
    Prometheus->>Predictor: Scrape metrics<br/>ServiceMonitor

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 2: Distributed Training with Kueue

    participant TrainingOp as Training Operator
    participant KueueCtrl as Kueue Controller
    participant Scheduler as Volcano Scheduler
    participant TrainingPod as Training Pods<br/>Distributed Workers

    User->>Notebook: 1. Create PyTorchJob YAML
    Notebook->>TrainingOp: 2. Submit PyTorchJob CR<br/>kubectl apply
    TrainingOp->>KueueCtrl: 3. Webhook mutation<br/>Create Workload CR

    KueueCtrl->>KueueCtrl: 4. Check ClusterQueue quota
    KueueCtrl->>TrainingOp: 5. Admit workload<br/>Status update

    TrainingOp->>Scheduler: 6. Create training pods<br/>Kubernetes API
    Scheduler->>TrainingPod: 7. Gang schedule all pods<br/>PodGroup

    TrainingPod->>TrainingPod: 8. Distributed training<br/>torchrun (TCP internal)
    TrainingPod->>S3: 9. Save checkpoints<br/>HTTPS

    TrainingPod-->>TrainingOp: 10. Job completion
    TrainingOp-->>Dashboard: 11. Status update<br/>Kubernetes API

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 3: ML Pipeline Execution

    participant Elyra as Elyra (in Notebook)
    participant DSPOp as DS Pipelines Operator
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows Controller
    participant PipelinePod as Pipeline Step Pods
    participant Minio as Minio/S3<br/>Artifacts
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB<br/>Metadata

    User->>Elyra: 1. Create pipeline<br/>visual editor
    Elyra->>DSPOp: 2. Submit pipeline YAML<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    DSPOp->>Argo: 3. Create Workflow CR<br/>Kubernetes API

    Argo->>PipelinePod: 4. Execute pipeline steps<br/>Sequential pods
    PipelinePod->>Minio: 5. Read/write artifacts<br/>HTTP (S3 API)
    PipelinePod->>MariaDB: 6. Write metadata<br/>MySQL
    PipelinePod->>MariaDB: 7. Log lineage (MLMD)<br/>gRPC via Envoy

    Argo-->>Dashboard: 8. Workflow status<br/>Kubernetes API
    User->>Dashboard: 9. View pipeline run<br/>HTTPS (OAuth proxy)

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 4: Ray Cluster Distributed Compute

    participant KubeRayOp as KubeRay Operator
    participant CodeFlareOp as CodeFlare Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>GCS/Dashboard
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pods

    User->>Dashboard: 1. Create RayCluster CR<br/>kubectl/Dashboard
    Dashboard->>KubeRayOp: 2. Create RayCluster<br/>Kubernetes API
    KubeRayOp->>CodeFlareOp: 3. Webhook mutation<br/>Inject OAuth/mTLS

    CodeFlareOp->>RayHead: 4. Deploy head pod<br/>Kubernetes API
    CodeFlareOp->>RayWorker: 5. Deploy worker pods<br/>Kubernetes API

    RayHead->>RayHead: 6. Start GCS server<br/>TCP 6379
    RayWorker->>RayHead: 7. Connect via mTLS<br/>TCP mTLS

    CodeFlareOp->>Gateway: 8. Create Route with OAuth<br/>OpenShift Router
    User->>Gateway: 9. Access Ray dashboard<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)

    Notebook->>RayHead: 10. Submit Ray job<br/>ray.init() TCP 10001
    RayHead->>RayWorker: 11. Schedule tasks<br/>Internal Ray protocol

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 5: Model Fairness Analysis (TrustyAI)

    participant TrustyAIOp as TrustyAI Operator
    participant TrustyAISvc as TrustyAI Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PVC as Persistent Volume

    User->>TrustyAIOp: 1. Create TrustyAIService CR<br/>kubectl
    TrustyAIOp->>TrustyAISvc: 2. Deploy service<br/>Kubernetes API
    TrustyAIOp->>Predictor: 3. Patch InferenceService<br/>Payload processor

    Predictor->>TrustyAISvc: 4. Send inference payloads<br/>HTTPS (mTLS)
    TrustyAISvc->>PVC: 5. Store inference data<br/>Filesystem

    TrustyAISvc->>TrustyAISvc: 6. Calculate fairness metrics<br/>SPD, DIR (scheduled)
    TrustyAISvc->>Prometheus: 7. Export bias metrics<br/>HTTP /metrics

    User->>TrustyAISvc: 8. Query metrics API<br/>HTTPS (OAuth)
    Prometheus->>Dashboard: 9. Visualize in Grafana<br/>Dashboard integration
